tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The urine findings indicate a urinary tract infection (UTI) with Escherichia coli, evidenced by positive nitrites, leukocyte esterase, elevated leukocytes, presence of bacteria, and >100,000 CFU/mL E. coli. Hematuria and mild proteinuria are present. Glucosuria is noted and may warrant further evaluation for hyperglycemia or diabetes. No casts detected. Recommend clinical correlation and appropriate antimicrobial therapy.
Elias Höfig
male
